{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":33607,"name":"Leith Ketchell","username":"Leith","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/discourse.urho3d.io/leith/{size}/2384_2.png","created_at":"2019-09-12T07:58:39.333Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eHere‚Äôs a screen shot that shows an arc being drawn between two points on the surface of a sphere.\u003cbr\u003e\nNote the orange arc, drawn between the two purple vectors‚Ä¶\u003cbr\u003e\nI plan to use it as part of an orientation widget, to help visualize a proposed quaternion-slerp.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/4/4449c9550106fc3e89fe216ac5d4bbae65ad62b4.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/9K6yopw3OIDcda5ip2duZQQygew.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"Screenshot from 2019-09-12 17-35-40.jpg\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/4/4449c9550106fc3e89fe216ac5d4bbae65ad62b4_2_690x388.jpeg\" alt=\"Screenshot%20from%202019-09-12%2017-35-40\" data-base62-sha1=\"9K6yopw3OIDcda5ip2duZQQygew\" width=\"690\" height=\"388\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/4/4449c9550106fc3e89fe216ac5d4bbae65ad62b4_2_690x388.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/4/4449c9550106fc3e89fe216ac5d4bbae65ad62b4_2_1035x582.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/4/4449c9550106fc3e89fe216ac5d4bbae65ad62b4_2_1380x776.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/4/4449c9550106fc3e89fe216ac5d4bbae65ad62b4_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eScreenshot from 2019-09-12 17-35-40.jpg\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1920√ó1080 711 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse xlink:href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/a\u003e\u003c/div\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere‚Äôs the code:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cpre\u003e\u003ccode class=\"lang-auto\"\u003evoid DebugRenderer::AddArc(const Sphere\u0026amp; sphere, const Vector3\u0026amp; from, const Vector3\u0026amp; to, const Color\u0026amp; color, int steps, bool depthTest)\n{\n    Vector3 prevPoint, nextPoint;\n\n    float omega = Acos(from.DotProduct(to));\n    float d = Sin(omega);\n\n    for(float t=0; t\u0026lt;=1.0f; t+=1.0f / (float)steps){\n        prevPoint = nextPoint;\n        float s0 = Sin((1.0f - t) * omega);\n        float s1 = Sin(t * omega);\n        nextPoint = (from * s0 + to * s1) / d;\n        if(t\u0026gt;0)\n            AddLine(prevPoint*sphere.radius_+sphere.center_, nextPoint*sphere.radius_+sphere.center_, color, depthTest);\n    }\n}\u003c/code\u003e\u003c/pre\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThe two input vectors are assumed to be direction normals (from origin of sphere to each surface point).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eI hope others find this useful \u003cimg src=\"https://emoji.discourse-cdn.com/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9\" title=\":slight_smile:\" class=\"emoji\" alt=\":slight_smile:\"\u003e\u003c/p\u003e","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"updated_at":"2019-09-12T08:14:44.772Z","reply_count":0,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":3,"reads":26,"readers_count":25,"score":50.2,"yours":false,"topic_id":5568,"topic_slug":"debugrenderer-support-for-drawing-arcs-on-spheres","display_username":"Leith Ketchell","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"version":3,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"